        "content": "<p>Is there a definition of the \"function\"-property of a relation, in the sense of : <em>\"it associates every instance of the first type to exactly one instance of the second type\"</em>?<br>\nAnd if so, is there a method for turning a <code>rel α β</code> into <code>α → β</code>?</p>",
        "id": 221162008,
        "sender_full_name": "Marcus Rossel",
        "timestamp": 1609271830
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We have <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/relator.right_unique\">docs#relator.right_unique</a> and <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/relator.left_total\">docs#relator.left_total</a></p>",
        "id": 221314005,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1609446143
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(BTW, they should be made non-<code>class</code>es because we have 0 instances)</p>",
        "id": 221314026,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1609446179
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can use <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/classical.some\">docs#classical.some</a> to get <code>f : α → β</code> from <code>∀ x, ∃ y, r x y</code>.</p>",
